The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It specifically focuses on social networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the subcategories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and social computing (cs.SOC). The paper also proposes a novel auction mechanism, which could fall under the subcategory of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper deals with incentivizing buyers to propagate information, which could involve the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
